properties.headline: Dense Fog Advisory issued January 15 at 5:44AM CST until January 15 at 8:00AM CST by NWS San Angelo TX
properties.description:
...Dense Fog Developing Across Portions of West Central Texas...

The National Weather Service in San Angelo has issued a Dense Fog
Advisory, which is in effect until 8 AM CST this morning.

* VISIBILITIES...Dropping to near zero at times.

* TIMING...through mid morning.

* IMPACTS...Reduced visibility will create hazardous driving
conditions across portions of the Edwards Plateau this morning.
Areas along I-10 will be effected by near zero visibility at
times from Ozona to Sonora to Junction. Conditions will begin to
improve around mid morning.
properties.instruction:
A Dense Fog Advisory means visibilities will frequently be
reduced to one quarter mile or less. If driving... slow down, use
your low beams, and leave plenty of distance ahead of you.

NWSheadline: DENSE FOG ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 8 AM CST THIS MORNING
